    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-16T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-16T09:00:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-16T11:00:00-03:00"
                            >May 16, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 16—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. The American Chamber of Commerce has formally inquired whether the Embassy
                    will endeavor to obtain information from the Bank of Brazil regarding the amount
                    and disposition of the foreign exchange it has granted during the past 6 months.
                    An inquiry on this subject at this time would be construed as having been made
                    on behalf of the Department in connection with the impending conversations at
                    Washington. Does the Department desire this information or does it prefer that I
                    shall decline to accede to the request of the Chamber?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
